{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":917,"text":"So, I teach college students\nabout inequality and race in education,"},{"time":5761,"text":"and I like to leave my office open\nto any of my students"},{"time":8850,"text":"who might just want to see me to chat."},{"time":11405,"text":"And a few semesters ago,"},{"time":12976,"text":"one of my more cheerful\nstudents, Mahari,"},{"time":15905,"text":"actually came to see me"},{"time":17326,"text":"and mentioned that he was feeling\na bit like an outcast because he's black."},{"time":22001,"text":"He had just transferred to NYU\nfrom a community college"},{"time":24898,"text":"on a merit scholarship,"},{"time":26684,"text":"and turns out,"},{"time":28542,"text":"only about five percent\nof students at NYU are black."},{"time":31848,"text":"And so I started to remember"},{"time":33301,"text":"that I know that feeling\nof being an outsider"},{"time":35854,"text":"in your own community."},{"time":37558,"text":"It's partially what drew me to my work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":39801,"text":"At my university,"},{"time":41056,"text":"I'm one of the few\nfaculty members of color,"},{"time":43477,"text":"and growing up, I experienced\nmy family's social mobility,"},{"time":47326,"text":"moving out of apartments\ninto a nice house,"},{"time":50573,"text":"but in an overwhelmingly\nwhite neighborhood."},{"time":53293,"text":"I was 12,"},{"time":54467,"text":"and kids would say that were surprised\nthat I didn't smell like curry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":58443,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":59690,"text":"That's because school is in the morning,"},{"time":61659,"text":"and I had Eggo waffles for breakfast."}]},{"cues":[{"time":63555,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":65184,"text":"Curry is for dinner."}]},{"cues":[{"time":66437,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":68412,"text":"So when Mahari was leaving,"},{"time":69817,"text":"I asked him how he was coping\nwith feeling isolated."},{"time":72833,"text":"And he said that despite feeling lonely,"},{"time":75082,"text":"he just threw himself at his work,"},{"time":77182,"text":"that he built strategies around his grit"},{"time":79659,"text":"and his desire to be successful."},{"time":81945,"text":"A mentor of mine is actually\nDr. Angela Duckworth,"},{"time":84874,"text":"the psychologist at UPenn who has defined\nthis stick-to-itiveness of grit"},{"time":89765,"text":"as being \"the perseverance\nand passion for long-term goals.\""},{"time":93469,"text":"Angela's book has become a bestseller,"},{"time":95670,"text":"and schools across the country,"},{"time":97705,"text":"particularly charter schools,"},{"time":99444,"text":"have become interested in citing\n\"grit\" as a core value."},{"time":103320,"text":"But sometimes grit isn't enough,"},{"time":105330,"text":"especially in education."},{"time":107254,"text":"So when Mahari was leaving my office,"},{"time":109146,"text":"I worried that he might need\nsomething more specific"},{"time":111848,"text":"to combat the challenges\nthat he mentioned to me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":114760,"text":"As a sociologist,\nI also study achievement,"},{"time":118053,"text":"but from a slightly different perspective."},{"time":120256,"text":"I research students who have overcome\nimmense obstacles"},{"time":123453,"text":"related to their background."},{"time":125101,"text":"Students from low-income,"},{"time":126757,"text":"often single-parent households,"},{"time":128818,"text":"students who have been homeless,\nincarcerated or perhaps undocumented,"},{"time":133679,"text":"or some who have struggled\nwith substance abuse"},{"time":136132,"text":"or lived through violent or sexual trauma."}]},{"cues":[{"time":139319,"text":"So let me tell you about two\nof the grittiest people I've met."},{"time":143077,"text":"Tyrique was raised by a single mother,"},{"time":145775,"text":"and then after high school,\nhe fell in with the wrong crowd."},{"time":148653,"text":"He got arrested for armed robbery."},{"time":150569,"text":"But in prison, he started to work hard."},{"time":153051,"text":"He took college credit courses,"},{"time":154901,"text":"so when he got out,\nhe was able to get a master's,"},{"time":157571,"text":"and today he's a manager at a nonprofit."},{"time":160782,"text":"Vanessa had to move around a lot as a kid,"},{"time":163486,"text":"from the Lower East Side\nto Staten Island to the Bronx."},{"time":166877,"text":"She was raised primarily\nby her extended family,"},{"time":169872,"text":"because her own mother\nhad a heroin addiction."},{"time":172812,"text":"Yet at 15,"},{"time":173986,"text":"Vanessa had to drop out of school,"},{"time":175630,"text":"and she had a son of her own."},{"time":177313,"text":"But eventually, she was able\nto go to community college,"},{"time":180827,"text":"get her associate's,"},{"time":182346,"text":"then go to an elite college\nto finish her bachelor's."}]},{"cues":[{"time":186261,"text":"So some people might\nhear these stories and say,"},{"time":188809,"text":"\"Yes, those two definitely have grit."},{"time":190842,"text":"They basically pulled themselves up\nby the bootstraps.\""},{"time":194050,"text":"But that's an incomplete picture,"},{"time":196512,"text":"because what's more important"},{"time":198057,"text":"is that they had factors in their lives\nthat helped to influence their agency,"},{"time":202182,"text":"or their specific capacity"},{"time":203882,"text":"to actually overcome\nthe obstacles that they were facing"},{"time":207470,"text":"and navigate the system\ngiven their circumstances."}]},{"cues":[{"time":211176,"text":"So, allow me to elaborate."},{"time":212965,"text":"In prison, Tyrique\nwas actually aimless at first,"},{"time":216322,"text":"as a 22-year-old on Rikers Island."},{"time":218917,"text":"This is until an older detainee\ntook him aside"},{"time":222243,"text":"and asked him to help\nwith the youth program."},{"time":224808,"text":"And in mentoring youth,"},{"time":226275,"text":"he started to see his own mistakes\nand possibilities in the teens."},{"time":230365,"text":"This is what got him interested\nin taking college-credit courses."},{"time":233963,"text":"And when he got out,"},{"time":235167,"text":"he got a job with Fortune Society,"},{"time":237405,"text":"where many executives are people\nwho have been formerly incarcerated."},{"time":241543,"text":"So then he was able to get\na master's in social work,"},{"time":244234,"text":"and today, he even lectures\nat Columbia about prison reform."},{"time":249057,"text":"And Vanessa ..."},{"time":250573,"text":"well, after the birth of her son,"},{"time":252661,"text":"she happened to find a program\ncalled Vocational Foundation"},{"time":255965,"text":"that gave her 20 dollars biweekly,"},{"time":258005,"text":"a MetroCard"},{"time":259187,"text":"and her first experiences with a computer."},{"time":261397,"text":"These simple resources\nare what helped her get her GED,"},{"time":264765,"text":"but then she suffered\nfrom a very serious kidney failure,"},{"time":267644,"text":"which was particularly problematic\nbecause she was only born with one kidney."},{"time":271732,"text":"She spent 10 years on dialysis\nwaiting for a successful transplant."},{"time":276423,"text":"After that,"},{"time":277752,"text":"her mentors at community college\nhad kept in touch with her,"},{"time":280598,"text":"and so she was able to go,"},{"time":282259,"text":"and they put her in an honors program."},{"time":284382,"text":"And that's the pathway\nthat allowed her to become accepted"},{"time":287147,"text":"to one of the most elite colleges\nfor women in the country,"},{"time":290510,"text":"and she received her bachelor's at 36,"},{"time":293011,"text":"setting an incredible example\nfor her young son."}]},{"cues":[{"time":296782,"text":"What these stories primarily indicate\nis that teaching is social"},{"time":300995,"text":"and benefits from social scaffolding."},{"time":303384,"text":"There were factors\npushing these two in one direction,"},{"time":306218,"text":"but through tailored\nmentorship and opportunities,"},{"time":309091,"text":"they were able to reflect\non their circumstances"},{"time":311639,"text":"and resist negative influences."},{"time":314175,"text":"They also learned simple skills\nlike developing a network,"},{"time":317709,"text":"or asking for help --"},{"time":319374,"text":"things many of us in this room can forget\nthat we have needed from time to time,"},{"time":324202,"text":"or can take for granted."}]},{"cues":[{"time":326251,"text":"And when we think of people like this,"},{"time":328107,"text":"we should only think of them\nas exceptional, but not as exceptions."},{"time":332652,"text":"Thinking of them as exceptions absolves us"},{"time":335501,"text":"of the collective responsibility\nto help students in similar situations."},{"time":340274,"text":"When Presidents Bush, Obama\nand now even Trump,"},{"time":343902,"text":"have called education\n\"the civil rights issue of our time,\""},{"time":347624,"text":"perhaps we should treat it that way."},{"time":350119,"text":"If schools were able to think\nabout the agency that their students have"},{"time":353855,"text":"and bring to the table\nwhen they push them,"},{"time":356372,"text":"what students learn can become\nmore relevant to their lives,"},{"time":359395,"text":"and then they can tap into those internal\nreservoirs of grit and character."}]},{"cues":[{"time":365090,"text":"So this here --"},{"time":366653,"text":"My student Mahari"},{"time":368392,"text":"got accepted to law school\nwith scholarships,"},{"time":371641,"text":"and not to brag,"},{"time":373181,"text":"but I did write one of his letters\nof recommendation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":375728,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":377340,"text":"And even though I know hard work\nis what got him this achievement,"},{"time":381322,"text":"I've seen him find\nhis voice along the way,"},{"time":383453,"text":"which as someone who's grown up\na little bit shy and awkward,"},{"time":387318,"text":"I know it takes time and support."},{"time":389655,"text":"So even though\nhe will rely a lot on his grit"},{"time":392814,"text":"to get him through\nthat first-year law school grind,"},{"time":396013,"text":"I'll be there as a mentor for him,"},{"time":398442,"text":"check in with him from time to time,"},{"time":400498,"text":"maybe take him out to get some curry ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":402506,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":403617,"text":"so that he can keep growing his agency\nto succeed even more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":407392,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":408567,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}